Levio Consulting is seeking an experienced HCL WebSphere developer (English, Remote Role)




Reporting to the Manager, IT, the candidate will work within a SCRUM team, in an agile model, to build, deploy, and support our clients (Long term).




Your role more specifically:

· Evaluate and recommend solutions for business requirements

· Work from development to deployment and support; manage data and code across environments

· Ensure and maintain high standards of quality for technical solutions working across cross-functional teams

· As needed, take part in drafting and executing system test scenarios, builds, and deployments

· As a support team member, troubleshoot and debug production/non-production issues

Your Profile:

· Hold a college or university diploma in computer science

· At least five (5) years of experience in Java web application development;

· Hands-on experience with HCL Commerce version 9 (mandatory -required)

· Knowledge or work experience with Lucidworks Fusion (an asset)

· Relevant expertise in JAVA WEB system development

· Expert in Java programming (JEE, EJB, Servlet, JSP, Struts, JSF);

· Experience with Oracle SQL, JS (ES5-6), jQuery, Ajax et CSS (SASS);

· Experience working on an agile environment and good understanding of DevOps tools and techniques (an asset)

· Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and follow-up skills

Other requirements:

· Experience with 3rd party integration using REST and SOAP services

· Experience with Solr (an asset);

· Show team spirit and a sense of initiative;

· Have analysis and synthesis skills;

· Ability to explain and transfer one’s knowledge;

· Ability to adapt easily to change;

· Ability to listen to clients;

· Be well-structured;

· Be well-organized, have the sense of service and be motivated by quality results;

· Fluent English language, bilingual English & French is an asset. (spoken and written)








If this sounds like your skill set and you can work within the Eastern Time Zone in a full remote capacity, please apply today!
